title: Dane Dorahy
text: Dane Dorahy (), also known by the <a href="nickname">nickname</a> of "Doz", is an Australian former professional <a href="rugby%20league">rugby league</a> footballer who played in the 1990s and 2000s. He played at club level for <a href="Western%20Suburbs%20Magpies">Western Suburbs</a> (<a href="List%20of%20Western%20Suburbs%20Magpies%20players">Heritage № 1029</a>), <a href="Warrington%20Wolves">Warrington Wolves</a> (non-First team), <a href="Rochdale%20Hornets">Rochdale Hornets</a>, <a href="Wakefield%20Trinity">Wakefield Trinity Wildcats</a> (<a href="List%20of%20Wakefield%20Trinity%20players">Heritage № 1165</a>), <a href="Hull%20Kingston%20Rovers">Hull Kingston Rovers</a> (<a href="List%20of%20Hull%20Kingston%20Rovers%20players">Heritage №</a>) and <a href="Halifax%20R.L.F.C.">Halifax</a> (<a href="List%20of%20Halifax%20R.L.F.C.%20players">Heritage № 1172</a>), as a , or . He is the son of former international player and coach, <a href="John%20Dorahy">John Dorahy</a>.
